          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "3",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I am a parent of a Jr. KG student and I am extremely disappointed with how weekly “celebration days” are handled. Parents are expected to check the school app every morning and send children dressed according to the theme. If the child comes in uniform, teachers/didi question us publicly during pickup in front of other staff and parents.\nOne day, I explained that I have two children, including one in 6th grade, and it is difficult to arrange special outfits every time. Instead of understanding, the class teacher said other parents also have two children and that I am not exceptional. I was also told that the principal questions teachers about why my child is not dressed up, which clearly shows unnecessary pressure is being passed on to parents.\nAs a parent, this feels embarrassing, disrespectful, and emotionally stressful. Activities are welcome, but public questioning and comparison with other parents is not acceptable. Better communication and sensitivity towards families are seriously needed",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
